        "timestamp": "2020-12-07 23:12:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> Patch Set 4:\n> \n> > Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n> > \n> > Version bump is required part of any functional/non-functional updates -  dont see either in this case.\n> \n> It is for future development, we do not want to create jars and push them to nexus(daily jenkis job) of version which was already released.\n\nThere wouldn't be any conflict as the jars released are under different repo (nexus/releases) and daily jobs are pushed into snapshot. As there are anyway changes planned for SDK in H, would suggest incrementing the version along with update.",
